.TH "HTMLBUTTONELEMENT.COMMAND" "3JS" "October 17, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLButtonElement.command \- HTMLButtonElement: command property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]command\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLButtonElement\f[R] interface gets and sets the action to be
performed on an element being controlled by this button.
For this to have an effect, \f[CR]commandfor\f[R] must be set.
.PP
It reflects the \f[CR]command\f[R] HTML attribute.
.SH VALUE
A string.
See the \f[CR]command\f[R] attribute for valid values.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic example
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqtoggleBtn\(dq commandfor=\(dqmypopover\(dq command=\(dqtoggle\-popover\(dq>
  Toggle popover
</\f[B]button\f[R]>

<\f[B]div\f[R] popover id=\(dqmypopover\(dq>
  <\f[B]button\f[R] commandfor=\(dqmypopover\(dq command=\(dqhide\-popover\(dq>Hide popover</\f[B]button\f[R]>
</\f[B]div\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] popover = document.getElementById(\(dqmypopover\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] toggleBtn = document.getElementById(\(dqtoggleBtn\(dq);

toggleBtn.command = \(dqshow\-popover\(dq;
.EE
.SS Using custom values for commands
In this example, three buttons have been created using custom values for
\f[CR]command\f[R].
Each button targets the same image using the \f[CR]commandfor\f[R]
attribute.
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]div\f[R] class=\(dqcontrols\(dq>
  <\f[B]button\f[R] commandfor=\(dqthe\-image\(dq command=\(dq\-\-rotate\-left\(dq>Rotate Left</\f[B]button\f[R]>
  <\f[B]button\f[R] commandfor=\(dqthe\-image\(dq command=\(dq\-\-reset\(dq>Reset</\f[B]button\f[R]>
  <\f[B]button\f[R] commandfor=\(dqthe\-image\(dq command=\(dq\-\-rotate\-right\(dq>Rotate Right</\f[B]button\f[R]>
</\f[B]div\f[R]>

<\f[B]img\f[R]
  id=\(dqthe\-image\(dq
  src=\(dq/shared\-assets/images/examples/dino.svg\(dq
  alt=\(dqdinosaur head rotated 0 degrees\(dq />
.EE
.PP
An event listener is attached to the image using the \f[CR]command\f[R]
event.
When one of the buttons is clicked, the listener runs code based on the
custom \f[CR]command\f[R] value assigned to the button, rotating the
image and also updating it\(cqs \f[CR]alt\f[R] text to indicate the new
angle of the image.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] image = document.getElementById(\(dqthe\-image\(dq);

image.addEventListener(\(dqcommand\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]let\f[R] rotate = parseInt(event.target.style.rotate || \(dq0\(dq, 10);
  \f[B]if\f[R] (event.command === \(dq\-\-reset\(dq) {
    rotate = 0;
    event.target.style.rotate = \(ga${rotate}deg\(ga;
  } \f[B]else\f[R] \f[B]if\f[R] (event.command === \(dq\-\-rotate\-left\(dq) {
    rotate = rotate === \-270 ? 0 : rotate \- 90;
    event.target.style.rotate = \(ga${rotate}deg\(ga;
  } \f[B]else\f[R] \f[B]if\f[R] (event.command === \(dq\-\-rotate\-right\(dq) {
    rotate = rotate === 270 ? 0 : rotate + 90;
    event.target.style.rotate = \(ga${rotate}deg\(ga;
  }
  event.target.alt = \(gadinosaur head rotated ${rotate} degrees\(ga;
});
.EE
